  %h1 Data & Privacy Policy
  
  %p
    Fakturo ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Data & Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, store, and safeguard information when you use our website and related services ("Services"). By using our Services, you agree to the terms outlined in this policy.

  %hr/

  %h2 1. Information We Do Not Collect
  %p
    We do
    %strong not collect or store any Personally Identifiable Information (PII)
    such as your name, email address, IP address, or any other information that can be used to identify you individually.
  %p
    Our services are designed to operate without requiring or storing any personal user data in our systems.

  %h2 2. File Uploads and Data Processing
  %ul
    %li
      Files you upload for processing (e.g., documents, images, etc.) are
      %strong stored temporarily and securely
      using
      %strong encryption both at rest and in transit.
      
    %li
      These files are
      %strong automatically deleted
      after the processing is complete. We do
      %strong not retain
      any user-uploaded content after this point.
    %li
      All file handling is done in a secure and isolated environment to protect your data integrity and privacy.

  %h2 3. Use of Generative AI (GenAI)
  %ul
    %li
      We utilize Generative AI (GenAI) models
      %strong locally
      , within our own infrastructure or in-browser, where applicable.
    %li
      %strong No user data or inputs are sent to external APIs, third-party services, or cloud-based AI providers.
    %li
      All AI-related processing is performed in a secure, private environment and does
      %strong not involve sharing, storing, or logging
      your inputs or outputs with any third party.

  %h2 4. Cookies and Tracking
  %p
    We use minimal cookies and similar technologies strictly for the functionality of the website (e.g., session management, UI preferences). We
    %strong do not use tracking cookies
    or share usage data with third-party analytics or advertising platforms.

  %h2 5. Third-Party Access
  %p
    We do
    %strong not sell, rent, share, or disclose
    any user data to third parties.

  %h2 6. Data Security
  %p We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your data during its short lifespan on our systems. This includes:
  %ul
    %li
      %strong Encryption
      (TLS for data in transit, AES for data at rest)
    %li
      %strong Temporary file storage
      with automatic deletion
    %li
      %strong Local-only AI processing

  %h2 7. Your Rights
  %p
    Any data related to your use of our Services can be deleted at any time directly from the website.

  %h2 8. Children's Privacy
  %p
    Our Services are not intended for use by individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect or store information from children.

  %h2 9. Changes to This Policy
  %p
    We may update this Data & Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page. Your continued use of the Services after changes are made constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.

